	dct:description " Helicopter-triggered lightning occurs mainly over the North Sea in winter (October–April) often when there is little or no natural lightning—implying the helicopter itself triggers the strike. Output is 3 risk levels where 0=none 1=low 2=moderate 3=high."@en ;
